The National Working Committee (NWC) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) postponed its Local Government Congress. The exercise to elect one LGA National Delegate, earlier scheduled for Thursday, May 5, 2022, has been postponed till further notice. PDP in a statement by its National Publicity Secretary, Hon. Debo Ologunagba, Wednesday, hinted that a new date will be announced in due course. “The NWC regrets any inconveniences the postponement may have caused,” the statement added. The party enjoined all leaders, critical stakeholders and members across the country to please take note.